<span id="freeTextContainer13717285105902379546">King Bidgood&apos;s in the Bathtub by Audrey Wood is also characterized by simple clean vocabulary but has some of the most miraculous and intricate drawings I&apos;ve ever seen, by Don Wood. I love the premise (of refusing to get out of a bath) and I can still stair for hours at the detail in those amazing full page illustrations. (It helps that the artist&apos;s model for the king, Harry Bidgood, was a family friend.)</span>
